<a name="31550498"></a>
<div id="answer-31550498" class="answer" data-answerid="31550498"  itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Answer">
    <table>
        <tr>
            <td class="votecell">
                

<div class="vote">
        <input type="hidden" name="_id_" value="31550498">
        <a class="vote-up-off" title="This answer is useful">up vote</a>
        <span itemprop="upvoteCount" class="vote-count-post ">103</span>
        <a class="vote-down-off" title="This answer is not useful">down vote</a>




</div>

            </td>
            


<td class="answercell">
    <div class="post-text" itemprop="text">
<p>I wish someone shared this site with me long ago <a href="http://cors.io/">http://cors.io/</a> it would have saved a ton of time compared to building and relying on my own proxy. However, as you move to production, having your own proxy is the best bet since you still control all aspects of your data.</p>

<p>All you need:</p>

<p><code>http://cors.io/?http://HTTP_YOUR_LINK_HERE</code></p>
    </div>
