<td class="answercell">
    <div class="post-text" itemprop="text">
<p>You can bypass the problem by using YQL to proxy the request through Yahoo's servers. It is just a few lines of code:</p>

<pre><code>var yql_url = 'https://query.yahooapis.com/v1/public/yql';
var url = 'your api url';

$.ajax({
    'url': yql_url,
    'data': {
        'q': 'SELECT * FROM json WHERE url="'+url+'"',
        'format': 'json',
        'jsonCompat': 'new',
    },
    'dataType': 'jsonp',
    'success': function(response) {
        console.log(response);
    },
});
</code></pre>

<p>Here's the link with an explanation: <a href="https://vverma.net/fetch-any-json-using-jsonp-and-yql.html" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://vverma.net/fetch-any-json-using-jsonp-and-yql.html</a></p>
    </div>
