        <td class="comment-text js-comment-text-and-form">
            <div style="display: block;" class="comment-body">
                <span class="comment-copy">I have an IIS site which is local that is hosting my API. I have an external site which is accessed outside the local network. I am trying to execute the API from the external site, I have CORS enabled for the external site (e.g. <code>[EnableCors(origins: &quot;http:&#47;&#47;websitelink.com&quot;, headers: &quot;*&quot;, methods: &quot;*&quot;)]</code> but it is not working. Any idea? <a href="https://forums.asp.net/p/2117965/6126338.aspx?p=True&amp;t=636259359932511119" rel="nofollow noreferrer">forums.asp.net/p/2117965/&hellip;</a></span>
                    &ndash;&nbsp;<a href="/users/837722/si8"
                       title="4,395 reputation"
                       class="comment-user">Si8</a>
